{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 369512, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Erlinn", "body": "Beta testers have found a place ingame where the cinematic is thought to have taken place (tall cliff overlooking a large canyon, etc.) with a big ol' hole in the ground where a frost wyrm could have sprung from the ice, and it's called \"Sindragosa's Fall\". This has lead to the conclusion that the wyrm in the cinematic is, indeed, Sindragosa.", "date": "2008-09-05T15:27:37-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 370141, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "XilDarkz", "body": "Further elaboration on Erlinn's post:\r\n\r\nSindragosa's Fall seems like the name of an area where she died, and she is a notable dragon to die. In the cinematic, it is speculated that you see the Lich King's revival of her into his command. \r\n\r\nShe will possibly be the Illidan of Wrath, while Arthas himself will be the Kil'Jaeden.", "date": "2008-09-06T13:12:08-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 404419, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "29778", "body": "On a series of quest in Icecrown, you get a cut-scene after a quest in Sindragosa's Fall. Arthas raises Sindragosa from the ice in the cut-scene. So the frost wrym in WotLK cinematic is supposedly Sindragosa as the cut-scene precisely shows the same event as the cinematic.", "date": "2008-10-13T02:55:56-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-10-13T02:57:14-05:00", 2, "29778"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 414050, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Siralex", "body": "One of the longest-awaited for bosses/encounters to be unveiled (given the 4-horsemen took foreverrr).  But, the opening scene when the encounter is initiated tells the whole story behind how well-thought this encounter was (even though it was basically a resistance/gear check)", "date": "2008-10-20T21:02:26-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 421784, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "236106", "body": "has one of the most kick-ass entrance animations for a boss ever, i mean flying bones, who'd ever thought of that", "date": "2008-10-27T07:57:54-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 455785, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dubilas", "body": "Did anyone fight him already in wotlk? If so, is fr needed at all?\r\n\r\nThanks in advance...", "date": "2008-11-19T10:55:05-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Of course some people had some items from TBC left, but not more than few items per person - dont think any of the people we had in the raid was in a SWP guild in TBC. And yes, of course most people had already done a bunch of heroics - I never said we didnt and I would really expect anyone going to Naxx to have done some heroics. We werent using flasks, though - which I could imagine many others doing, especially if theyre struggling.  That doesnt really change what I said anyway - I simply said: \"First time in Naxx we did it with 2 healers and no frost resist apart from totem/aura\" in a repl", "creationdate": "2008-11-19T10:55:06-06:00", "id": 370814, "rating": 0, "commentid": 455785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "116607", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just did him in 10 man naxx, most of us actually being at Sapphiron for the first time (people stopped playing in old naxx before we got to 4H ect) and it only took us 4-5 tries to kill him without any use of FR gear. We did have a shaman for the totem, though.  It did help a lot having 2 priests I imagine. :)", "creationdate": "2008-11-19T17:10:04-06:00", "id": 362155, "rating": 3, "commentid": 455785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "116607", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If youre doing it with 3 healers and they go OOM that fast youre doing something wrong. Either the healers are using their mana wrong or people are taking way too much damage (such as standing in blizzard for too long, getting tail swipes ect). As I said, we did it without frost resistance (apart from totem) on our first run with 2 healers - it wasnt easy, but when we organised the healing a bit (one healer focusing on melee, other on casters) it wasnt really super hard either considering we all dinged 80 the same week.", "creationdate": "2008-11-29T14:42:36-06:00", "id": 365184, "rating": 0, "commentid": 455785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "116607", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "these details are all fine, but they dont help us. We tried it tonight with 3 healers. A number of us were already half heroic-epic and naxx geared, but we still didnt make it. Either the raid received too little healing, or the raid received enough healing but then the tank died because the healers were too busy healing the raid. Gief constructive reply's, plz.   Also, in before your healers suck, your tank sucks, and L2P", "creationdate": "2008-12-14T19:33:03-06:00", "id": 370912, "rating": 0, "commentid": 455785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Omegastar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I don't understand what can be so hard in healing this enounter. Got in on 2nd try. It's just that easy.", "creationdate": "2009-03-05T15:25:54-06:00", "id": 392394, "rating": 0, "commentid": 455785, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Deivijs", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 469951, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Fugazi", "body": "We tried him on 10 man and we just get completely destroyed. We haven't got any problems with any boss before so... My friend in other guild have exactly same problem - they are destroyed and got him most to like 85%.\n\nThe problem is healing, so much is needed that our 3 healers could not handle it at all - they are going oom in no time. I do not know what is the problem but this boss seems to be nightmare compared to all bosses before him.\n\nEDIT: So 2 months passed and I dig this. We killed him like week later quite easily and tactic was simply \"all non-healers go craft one piece of FrR set\". Add FrR aura/totem to that and you will sit on 200+ FrR (healers on 130) which will help a lot. However keep in mind that more than once piece will nerf your dps too much and healers cannot really equip this at all as they need their stats for this fight.", "date": "2008-11-25T15:57:40-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-18T06:36:17-06:00", 1, "Fugazi"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 472391, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Asora", "body": "In 10 man he does 1200 Frost damage each sec to everyone in the raid before slain.\r\nIn 25 man he does 1600 Frost damage each sec to everyone in the raid before slain.\r\nSapphiron has approximately 4,250,000 hit points in the 10 man version.\r\nAnd has approximately 11,870,000 hit points in the 25 man version.\r\n\r\nI would imagine it beeing easyer to do without Frost res in the 25man version as you bring more healers and different classes, in the 10man you bring at most 3 healers and 1-2 aoe healers, my guild 1 shoted every wing in nax and we had problems at sapp due to the healers still beeing in t5-6 and partly heroic gear.\r\n\r\nWe're giving it another try tomorrow with everyone in full frost res gear, wich is by the way easy obtainable with cheap and few mats.(Think blizzard are aiming these sets for the casual 10 man progressing guilds)\r\nThese sets are called\r\nPlate - Icebane\r\nBelt - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43587\r\nBoots - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43588\r\nChest - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43586\r\n\r\nLeather - Polar\r\nBelt - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43591\r\nBoots - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43592\r\nChest - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43590\r\n\r\nMail - Icy Scale\r\nBelt - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43594\r\nBoots - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43595\r\nChest - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43593\r\n\r\nCloth - Glacial\r\nBelt - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43584\r\nBoots - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43585\r\nChest - http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43583\r\n\r\nHope this helps for some, other then the damage over time, he is basicly a tank & spank with blizzard around the room, phase two is just spreading out at start and running behind two players beeing \"Ice tombed\" to Line of sight he's \"Deep breath\" wich is a frost bomb he puts in the middle of the room shortly after freezeing two random players of the raid.\r\n\r\nAsora - Invisus", "date": "2008-11-26T18:37:14-06:00", "rating": 46, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-01T16:52:30-06:00", 2, "Asora"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 472942, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "94427", "body": "Big note: If a melee type is still attacking Sapphiron in the air and gets ice blocked, make sure you aren't touching the ice block when the frost breath (bomb) hits, or you will still get hit. Leave some space between it.\n\nThis is coming from experience. I've seen people humping the block trying to melee Sapphiron with some auto attacks through it who then got pwned, while others behind the same block survived.", "date": "2008-11-27T01:45:58-06:00", "rating": 21, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-02-02T01:30:55-06:00", 2, "94427"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 482626, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "235903", "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nKaoswarr said in 2006 \"Frost Immunity: Immune to any frost based attacks.\" \r\n\r\nDoes anyone know if this is still true? We have not reached him yet but i was wondering if I could tank him as a Frost DK. I think Acclimation would help alot in this fight, or am I going to have to respec blood because he is immune to 70% of my dmg?", "date": "2008-12-01T12:18:03-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "No. The whole idea of bosses being immune to specific schools of damage seems to have gone away long ago.", "creationdate": "2011-02-18T20:24:33-06:00", "id": 226292, "rating": 2, "commentid": 482626, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Kanariya", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 490731, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "27710", "body": "in wrath you no longer see resist for spell misses, you see the actual miss message.\r\n\r\nIE as a priest if I cast Mind Blast at this boss and my 0 hit in holy gear causes the spell to miss, I see just that, a miss. But if say I'm dueling another priest who has Shadow Protection up (130+resistance), and the spell is resisted, I see just that, a resist  message.\r\n\r\nBlizzard most likely did this to help people better understand that Resist used to mean you weren't hit capped, and were stacking penetration believing it would reduce/eliminate resist messages.\r\n\r\nTLDR: If a frost dk/mage is seeing the word RESIST, the boss has resistance, if they are seeing MISS they need more +hit gear", "date": "2008-12-05T02:11:22-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 498276, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lormus", "body": "Info on his resistance to frost is definitely untrue as of live build. He does have frost resistance.\r\n\r\nI'm seeing 17% of my frosbolts resisted and I'm hit capped.", "date": "2008-12-08T16:40:07-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-08T16:40:47-06:00", 1, "lormus"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 498696, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "116607", "body": "The answer is on this page http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=28531 - its every second according to this. Honestly I didnt really notice the time interval myself, I was more focused on healing the damage taken (I was the one posting we did it with 2 priests on our first run with totem/aura only).\r\n\r\nThe raid does take a lot of damage, especially if DPS dont help the healers. They can help the healers by doing two things:\r\n1: Stay out of blizzard and avoid tail swipe - and dont get cleaves. This is pretty obvious and should be basic for every DPS - but sadly its not always, so be sure to remind people.\r\n2: Stay in groups. This can be a bit tricky from time to time as people have to run from blizzards - but with a little coordination its not a problem really. What we did the first time was making 2 camps - a melee camp and a caster camp. We gave a raidmark to a player in each camp and told everyone else to follow that guy as much as possible - we then assigned our priests to each their camp, both healing the maintank too.\r\n\r\nThis encounter was lot easier than what it felt like on our first try where healing felt really hard and people took a lot of damage. However, when we sorted the healing and the DPSers helped us out (what I wrote above) he went down fairly easy.", "date": "2008-12-08T21:07:09-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
