Environments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-06-10T23:19:17-05:00", 5, "WakemanCK"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 552688, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "195360", "body": "Sick of wiping to this boss from lack of heals, we decided to bring in some artillery: After the 16th wipe, everyone zoned out, took 1 hour to farm mats and check the AH, got their gear crafted, and zoned back in.\r\n\r\nIn this hour, we found that our Feral Druid had respecced resto and our Pally OT had brought along his healing gear.\r\n\r\nover 300 frost resist on whole raid, 4 healers and the OT in his healing gear. Only 1 tank and 4 dps. The fight was a joke, but took over 10 minutes.\r\n\r\nMain parts of the fight:\r\n-Learn to dodge the deep breath. You will not survive it. Either you learn to stand behind the iceblocks, or you will die.\r\n-Yes, Frost Resist is not NEEDED, but it HELPS, a LOT. Plus, as the MT, it will come in useful to tank Kel'Thuzad in the next fight (Frost Resist on the main tank helps a ton)\r\n-Take it easy. This is NOT a dps race, it's a survival fight. Help your healers and win.", "date": "2009-01-08T08:07:20-06:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 46, "id": 554189, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "288022", "body": "Ok some musings about the hardest heal fight in the instance.\r\n\r\n1. Pally healers are just shafted here. If we have a pally healer at this boss we tend to just have them assigned to MT heal and off heal when someone is real low(On a side note I'd love to be able to 2 heal this with a paladin but I have not as yet found a paladin geared/skilled enough to achieve this, im a resto shaman and go oom if I have to heal more than 6 people really)\r\n\r\n2. Priests/Shamans/Druids is what its all about here. Priests and Druids can keep a 5 man group alive here, whilst a shaman can easily keep 3 but with a little effort keep a 5 man group up.\r\n\r\n3. In the ground phase. Have the ranged groups split into two groups, left and right, all the melee are obviously all in the centre. Have 1 decurser for each of these groups(its much much better if the decurser is NOT a healer) assign 1 healer left 1 healer right, this splits up the blizzards as two are cast at once and if you are on one side all together there is a chance they can converge and wipe you\r\n\r\n4. In the air phase, have the whole raid run towards the entrance to the encounter this means you are away from the blizzards, that all the people dont have far to run for ice bolts it also means you are in range of all the aoe healers(nb if someone goes into an ice block at low hp it is essential for a healer to use a cooldown to save them the instant they come out). At this point any druid of any spec in your raid should use tranquility as it is an imba spell at the minute :)\r\n\r\nThe main things that cause a wipe here are :\r\n\r\n- Healer oom - This will come if you have poor dps or poor gear, only solution is to either swap people out or get more healers through respecs. Can also happen if people are being stupid and standing in blizzards\r\n\r\n- The boss healing up - This will only occur if people are not decursing. Explain to them this is priority 1 over another frostfirebolt/starfire etc\r\n\r\n- Unlucky Ice Bolts - You do need to keep your raid over about 50% hp at all times to avoid this, again this can be hard depending on healer spellpower but again more healers will resolve this problem.\r\n\r\nI hope this helps :)\r\n\r\nNb. The achievement 100 club is actually a really easy one as the frost resist set just doesnt seem to mitigate more than it gimps the healer mana and dps's dps.", "date": "2009-01-09T05:46:53-06:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 47, "id": 556481, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wrethched", "body": "For Sappihiron on Normal (10 Man) difficulty there is not much FrR needed to make the fight comfortable.\r\nOur guild usually only requires us to wear the chest piece of the FrR set which gives 115 FrR.\r\n\r\nIf we take a look at the FrR we can get from sets:\r\nChest + Aura/Totem = 245 FrR, Good\r\nBelt & Boots + Aura/Totem= 302 FrR, Very Good\r\nWhole Set + Aura/Totem = 417 FrR, Excellent\r\n\r\nIn my opinion \"Good\" is more than enough because otherwise you'll be turning in a lot of good stats as Mp/5 for an overload of Stamina and FrR, and as other people have stated you can easiliy do it without any FrR at all it's just that a little of it makes this fight so much easier.", "date": "2009-01-10T15:46:13-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 48, "id": 557824, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TMWNN", "body": "Twice Frost Breath wiped my pickup raid during the first air phase despite our hiding behind iceblocked people. Our mistake was running too close to the entrance; the little bits of \"snow\" on the ground raised us enough to be hit. Once we made sure to not be on the snowy ground we were fine. It's still good strategy to gather in one place to make sure we can reach an ice block quickly, of course, and the doorway is as good a place as any; just not too close.", "date": "2009-01-11T12:34:02-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 49, "id": 558174, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "42591", "body": "If you are not a HOLY priest do not read\r\n\r\n\r\nhealing this boss was pretty intense.\r\n\r\nthe spell that you should use the most is prayer of mending.  \r\n\r\nspamming renew and circle of healing is very bad.  you would go out of mana even before he takes flight.  try your best not to use these unless it is mandatory.  \r\n\r\nlet prayer of mending carry you in the ground phase.\r\n\r\nwhen he flies out, use prayer of healing / CoH to top everyone off before he fires his frost bolt to freeze people.\r\n\r\nrinse and repeat", "date": "2009-01-11T17:21:01-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 558181, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "42591", "body": "the only way to win against sapphiron is to have a mage / druid  dispel the curse as soon as possible.\r\n\r\notherwise you'll be stuck at 80% after 3 flying phases", "date": "2009-01-11T17:23:55-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It's not necessary, but it will help greatly.  The first time we went in to attempt Sapphiron we didn't have anyone in the raid that could remove curses throughout the entire instance and we were still able to clear it.  Yes, it was harder, but not impossible.", "creationdate": "2009-01-17T12:47:25-06:00", "id": 73314, "rating": 1, "commentid": 558181, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Akumas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "or a resto shaman i'm sure you meant to say :)", "creationdate": "2009-01-20T06:15:22-06:00", "id": 73979, "rating": 3, "commentid": 558181, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "144901", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 560785, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "303182", "body": "Mages, note that Frost Ward is your friend.  Any help you can give your healers by resisting damage for x amount of seconds is a huge help.  I have found it works well when you're positioned behind the ice blocks, makes it a bit easier to get through that mess.  I also use it when a blizzard is first dropped on me, if I can't get out of it fast enough.  \r\n\r\nHerbalists note that lifeblood, while not much of a HoT, can help as well.  This fight is about survivability, not a DPS race.", "date": "2009-01-13T09:37:49-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 561878, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Crowax", "body": "finally downed him yesterday.\r\n\r\ntanks: warr, druid <he was dpsing in cat on this fight>\r\nhealers: me <disc priest, specced for this fight only - actually i might stay in it>, holy pally, resto shaman\r\n5 dps: 2x rogue, shadowpriest <who died by not hiding behind blocks on 1st sapphiron's flight...no replenishment/hp from IVE>, hunter, dk\r\n\r\neasy fight. pally would decurse, also had FR aura. We've made our dps to wear some FR equip if they had it, but none on healers and tank. Also my SR prayer helped on missed decurses ;-)\r\n\r\ni really dunno how we could be wiping on him a day before soo many times. possibly, being a bit spread when he shoots icebolts is the biggest deal. and ofc hiding behind blocks they leave. didn't even use shadowfiend and i ended at ~20%, although u have to count in improved wisdom, mp5 flask and mana totems. had over 500 mp5 while casting", "date": "2009-01-14T04:14:32-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
