{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 563088, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Stigmata", "body": "No, he's correct.\r\n\r\n1.2k per person.\r\n10 people.\r\n\r\n12k to raid.", "date": "2009-01-14T23:31:35-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 566508, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Akumas", "body": "Based off personal experience, your healers will make or break this fight for you, depending on their skill level and ability to manage their mana pool due to the fight's long duration.\r\n\r\nThings I've seen that make this fight more difficult:\r\n(1) Having only one healer who can apply HoTs\r\n(2) Having people not remove Sapphiron's curse fast enough, or maybe not at all\r\n(3) Having unfortunate blizzard spamming on your melee over and over\r\n\r\nThings I've seen that make this fight much easier:\r\n(1) Having two or more healers that can apply HoTs\r\n(2) Getting fortunate with blizzard placement\r\n(3) Having a shadow priest's VE and VT\r\n\r\nIn terms of frost resist gear, I would recommend wearing one or two pieces if you're a new group or your healers can't quite get the job done.  However, I also want to stress that it's not necessary to wear any frost resist gear if you have skilled healers or multilpe healers that can HoT and AoE heal effectively.", "date": "2009-01-17T11:50:12-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-17T12:43:54-06:00", 4, "Akumas"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 566721, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "d3nyd", "body": "If you are a Death Knight, you can survive Sapph's Frost Breath.\r\n\r\nIcebound Fortitude + Anti-Magic Shell + Bone Shield will easily absorb MOST of the damage of this if you happen to get caught in its blast and you're not behind an Ice Bolted raid member. I found myself in that unfortunate situation, and popped all three of those abilities. I took only 5001 damage, with nearly 75,000 absorbed and 20,000 resisted. Unfortunately my HP was already below 5001, so I died anyway.\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso, if you aren't trying to push your luck and impress your raid and just kill the boss, you can trivialize the amount of damage you take from Frost Aura. Use IBF and AMS whenever the CDs are up and you're basically guaranteed to take the least amount of damage in the entire raid.", "date": "2009-01-17T15:00:58-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You realize AMS also reduces healing taken by 75% along with damage taken?  Because i hate that.  DK pops AMS, I need to drain life.  I  get ^&*!ed since i get 800 hp vs 3.5k.", "creationdate": "2009-08-25T12:09:28-05:00", "id": 422058, "rating": 0, "commentid": 566721, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "426611", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 57, "id": 570201, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "155412", "body": "Not sure why my comment was deleted... but here it goes again.\n\nSometimes Sapph's aura ticks faster, which causes huge head aches and frustration because the fight seems so easy when it doesn't tick fast.\n\nFast example from my guild:\nSuccessful wws log kill of Sapph - 1 tank, 7 dps, 2 healers.  The two healers combined put out roughly 2 million healing over just under 6 minutes, or about 5,700 heals per second.\n\nMass wipage best attempt on Sapph - 1 tank, 6 dps, 3 healers.  The three healers combined put out almost 4 million healing in 7 minutes, or about 9,500 heals per second (damn fine job, imo).\n\n\nI know what you're thinking, wait, the tooltip says it ticks 1200 per second, so shouldn't your raid have to put out 12,000 heals per second?\n\nTake a look at this log - 2 million damage in about 6 minutes http://wowwebstats.com/vt4tquxsatmpq?s=204317-218347\n\ncompared to this log - 3.3 million damage in 7 minutes http://wowwebstats.com/r5dpp5dbrbrcg?s=34043-56015\n\n(maybe it was wearing FrR gear, but i know in my guild's attempts, we never wear any FrR gear, so I'm positive this problem/bug does occur)\n\nConclusion? sometimes you're taking a ton more damage.  Good luck if that's the case.", "date": "2009-01-19T23:06:14-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Heals done over a period of time can in no way prove that the Frost Aura is doing more damage than expected.  The difference in healing could be from an undergeared tank, DPS standing in the Blizzard for too long, etc.  Also, 3.3 million is not almost 4 million.", "creationdate": "2009-05-07T14:20:30-05:00", "id": 96557, "rating": 2, "commentid": 570201, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "239711", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-19T23:14:45-06:00", 4, "155412"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 580157, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "311052", "body": "Just one thing about that Frost Breath, I am Speaking from experience that if you're a death knight with the Anti-Magic Shell improve specc You are able to earn 100+ runic power from the frost breath without taking the damage:)", "date": "2009-01-25T12:53:19-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
