{"commentv2": 1, "number": 72, "id": 639435, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "189117", "body": "You can actually stand on the grate on the wall and you will not get hit by deep breath, even tho I would not recommend as using this as a strategy to simplify the fight I would recommend this for \"Oh #$%^\" moments when you cant make the ice block.", "date": "2009-03-11T22:00:13-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is actually true. I tried it in Naxx 25 this week. Announced on vent that I may die as I hugged the wall. Did not get hit by frost breath.  =)   Uprate this man's post for those having problems with ice blocks.     As of 3.1, this technique no longer works.  *cough*  Found it out the hard way...", "creationdate": "2009-04-07T22:55:48-05:00", "id": 89966, "rating": 9, "commentid": 639435, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Toastie", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 73, "id": 643112, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "moriarti", "body": "There is no need to have either mages nor DKs sit this fight out.  Well, especially not the frost DKs.  The only blue gem ability that benefits DKs' dps is spell penetration.  Since you need 2 blue gems for the meta, you might as well have 20 spell penetration (10 from each of two dual color gems).   And since DKs benefit so little from agility, and so much from spell pen (if they are frost), your best back enchant is +35 spell pen.  That's full 55 spell pen right there.  Spell pen directly effects resistance: 1 point of pen=resistance reduced by 1 point.  As for the gems in your frost resist gear, just put 3 blue 20 spell pen gems.  You have 115 spell pen at that point.  You just might find yourself at the top of the dps chart for that fight for the full \"wtf\" effect.", "date": "2009-03-15T11:03:18-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-03-15T11:04:41-05:00", 1, "moriarti"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 74, "id": 653347, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "309760", "body": "Does anyone know if there's a glitch where Sapphiron will Ice Block a mages Water Elemental? My raid thinks that my pet basically caused a wipe, since he's immune to frost attacks and he wouldn't be frozen.", "date": "2009-03-23T21:09:28-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 75, "id": 664960, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "hackandmore", "body": "[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=26662]Berserk[/url] wont kill you...have the best healer(not by amount he heals but how much frost resist he has) focus on tank only...Shamans are perfect for this due to the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=55458]Chain Heal[/url]\n\nyou get more dmg per tick but that doesnt mean \"wipe all raid\" as stated\n\nIf you have high enough frost resist ure saved...\nHow we got our frost resist:\n[ol]\n[li][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48945]Frost Resistance Aura[/url] 130[/li]\n[li][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=58745]Frost Resistance Totem[/url] 130[/li]\n[li][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48470]Gift of the Wild[/url] 54[/li]\n[li][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=40215]Mighty Frost Protection Potion[/url] absorbs an average of 5k frost dmg[/li]\n[/ol]\nWe were lucky enough to have fewer dps and healers covered us\nwhen he went berserk we were down to 300-400k...no hunters for  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=19801]\nTranquilizing shot[/url]\n\nOur mage had alchemy and tons of pots.He claimed he never took frost dmg with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=43012]Frost Ward[/url] and the pots(actually he did 20k total :D)\n\nA pala had to pop [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=642]Divine Shield[/url] at the enrage thats all...\n\nBtw i had [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=43582]Titanium Frostguard Ring[/url] with a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=36767]Solid Dragon's Eye[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=59636]Enchant Ring - Stamina[/url] and a head frost resist enchant that got me to excellent frost resist status...\ntook like 150-200 dmg per tick and most of it was absorbed by pot", "date": "2009-04-03T17:57:44-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-03T18:00:30-05:00", 1, "hackandmore"]}
