{"commentv2": 1, "number": 78, "id": 671927, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "318930", "body": "I wonder if the name has any relation to sapphira from the book eragon :3", "date": "2009-04-10T12:50:04-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Sapphiron's name is a reference to his color - in life he was a blue dragon, and \"sapphire\" is a shade of blue (named for sapphire gems, which are most commonly blue).  His first appearance was in [i]Warcraft III: The Frozen Throne[/i], which was released in July 2003.", "creationdate": "2009-04-18T01:25:57-05:00", "id": 92038, "rating": 3, "commentid": 671927, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Egrem", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I think maybe the writer copied Warcraft. The entire lore for this game was written quite a long time ago. So it couldn't be from Eragon.", "creationdate": "2009-06-20T18:59:03-05:00", "id": 104905, "rating": 2, "commentid": 671927, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "338077", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
