{"commentv2": 1, "number": 85, "id": 776646, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "361624", "body": "OK, not exactly sure what was going on last night, but I have a theory....\r\n\r\nLast night I was running this on my hunter, my pet kept despawning.  I suspect that since I was close to max range, that my pet was going around to the back side and because Saph is so big, that it moved my pet out of range and he despawned.\r\n\r\nI had to resummon/call my pet 3-4 times during the fight.  Another hunter had the same issue last night as well.\r\n\r\nI'd like to hear if anyone else has another explanation, or at least let this serve as a cautionary note for hunters and possibly warlocks with pets out.  I'd done this fight before with my hunter and had not seen this previously, so I don't know if this is new, or if it's just an issue with where I was standing, but at any rate, pay attention to your pet and make sure he's still there, or else you'll lose out on some dps.", "date": "2009-07-13T09:21:10-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
