{"commentv2": 1, "number": 95, "id": 1136762, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "575688", "body": "3 Heroic  Crusaders managed to kill this cold pile of bones today 5  october 2010\r\n10 man ofc  and setup was warlock, holy paladin and warrior tank.. time used 14mins 47 seconds.. 13 secs off Berserk ;)\r\ngrate fun  and recomended fight for ppl looking for a laugh  :) enjoy\r\n(we use 0 FR )\r\nOlm, Jebarus and Bloodynora on SWC europe", "date": "2010-10-07T08:43:39-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-07T08:44:00-05:00", 1, "575688"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 96, "id": 1138148, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "45236", "body": "I'm positive you can 2 man this in 10 man with a gearscore of 5k-ish.  Our raid almost wiped, leaving shaman heals (me) and pally tank.  Keeping the tank and myself topped up with riptides and healing waves, we  kept out of the blizzard and I cleansed the Drain Life as soon as it was cast.  We kept the battle alive for 15 minutes and we were able to take him down from about 40% to less than 10% before he enraged. I have no doubt a focused team could duo him.", "date": "2010-10-09T03:28:04-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can 2 man this. My disc priest friend Eziel and I just did it. I'm a balance druid with resil for crit cap around 6300gs and we vanquished the beast in 12 minutes 36 seconds. We were on a roll after 2 manning heroic forge of souls. Very fun, and highly recommended. Amazing how much the game changes. I remember wiping to this with 10 people. Also used no frost resist.  Kembo Feathermoon", "creationdate": "2010-10-11T03:45:41-05:00", "id": 186057, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1138148, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "676707", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-09T03:37:06-05:00", 3, "45236"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 97, "id": 1140286, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "677287", "body": "Just two-manned him.\nWe came as shaman (me) and prot paladin (5500 gs offspec).\n\n1st try we went as 6k gs healer and tank but ended up with berserking rage on 40% hp.\n\nThen I specced enhance (5.8k gs) and we downed him on 3rd try having 15 seconds b4 enrage.\n\nHere are some tips if you are going to duo him.\n\n1) He doesn't hit even early icecrown tank hard. On 1st try my paladin friend was going just fine with earth shield and most of time I was \"dpsing\" boss. Aura isn't a problem too - it seems to be mostly outhealed by JoL and healing stream totem. I think that way better geared tank won't require healing at all.\n\n2) The pain in ass is drain life. If you can't dispell it you need to outheal it. [spell=28542 domain=www] - it really does like 20k damage and will apply to both of you. So if you are tank+hybrid and can't dispell you should screw DPS and heal up.\n\n3) Both of you will receive a personal Ice Block so you don't need to hide on air phase.\n\n4) If noone of you is a healer you should think about dealing with Blizzard. [spell=28547 domain=www] - it will hit for 3.5-4.5k every two seconds. 1st thing is that boss has HUGE hitbox and dps mate has lot of space to move. 2nd thing is that blizz seems to \"follow\" a person, so most of fight we were spinning boss like dark side Halion and got almost no blizzard hits at all.\n\n5) The enrage timer is 15 minutes which means that you two should pull like 4.7k dps together. But.\n - Ofc it's not hard if you just pump Patchwerk-like boss. \n- Flying phase also shortens the time you can dps the boss. He'll fly for like 15 seconds every 45 seconds. Roughly said, you'll waste 25% of time in ice blocks. 15 mins - 20% = 12.25 minutes and it's 5.7k dps to down him. \n- You'll waste time moving from blizzard, healing drain life and keeping up your tank which means even more time, damage and mana loss.\n\n\nMargerie (Ru-Soulflayer)\n\n\nHope this helps. Srry for bad english, we russians aren't good in it :)", "date": "2010-10-11T20:09:29-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-11T20:45:36-05:00", 6, "677287"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 98, "id": 1311118, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Incarcerated", "body": "Just soloed this as a blood dk (38/0/3). Beat the enrage by about 1 min.\r\nWiped once to enrage timer at 1.1m because i tried to kite him to avoid blizzard damage and used too much tank gear.\r\n\r\nHandy tips for soloers:\r\nDon't use purely tank gear. try to mix and match (I used dps trinkets and 3 dps armor items) otherwise you won't beat the enrage!\r\nMove around the boss to avoid the blizzard but try not to move him. The more movement, the less damage you can get on it and you want about 400-500k damage per air phase to beat the enrage.\r\nUse Anti-Magic Shell after you break free from the ice block and if you get into trouble with the blizzards.\r\nUse all available cooldowns and potions if you have them.\r\n\r\nWill be posting a Youtube guide soon.\r\n\r\nIncarcerated - Burning Steppes", "date": "2011-01-26T19:09:56-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 99, "id": 1331764, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nobbel", "body": "A video guide explaining how you can solo Sapphiron as a lvl 85 paladin:\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jzD9FsvHtoM\r\n\r\nNobbel", "date": "2011-02-11T11:06:12-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "New 4.3 version: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-NUsMxuYtZs&hd=1 Tacs are the same, fight is a lot easier", "creationdate": "2012-01-07T09:44:02-06:00", "id": 505722, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1331764, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 384, "username": "Nobbel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 100, "id": 1358998, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Delaios", "body": "Soloable as a Marskman hunter. Damage to your pet is easily healible with Mend Pet (a turtle or beetle isn't needed). Saph will hit you for 1.2k frost damage every few seconds and he'll put a shadow de-buff on you, but with Spirit Bond and Chimera Shot to heal you, it's manageable (ended with 80+% health after using Gift of the Naaru once). \nHave your pet tank Saph in the centre of the room. You just DPS Saph and kite around Saph in Fox Aspect if any of the blizzards come near.", "date": "2011-03-06T06:51:44-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just adding on here.  Keep Chimera Shot on CD and popping ChS, Readiness, ChS when you can without overhealing is nice too, although not necessary.  Feign Death will remove all the blizzards in the area for a few minutes if that helps anyone at all.", "creationdate": "2011-03-14T21:47:36-05:00", "id": 232282, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1358998, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zyland", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-03-06T06:52:34-06:00", 1, "Delaios"]}
