{"commentv2": 1, "number": 102, "id": 1412355, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Skorpion9x", "body": "Easily soloed as Feral Druid in ilvl 368 dps gear, tank spec. \r\n\r\nThe fight is pretty straight forward. Just dps him in bear form, avoid blizzards. Use defensive cooldowns if necessary. I don't even think I needed them. I used barkskin when it was off cd, usually during a life drain. To make the fight go a little faster, I would go cat form during air phases and hit him before and after being an ice cube. If I was lucky, I could get a 5 point rip before getting ice cubed, and again afterwards before he landed. Most of the time, though, I would get cubed with 4 combo points and have to wait till after to put up the rip.", "date": "2011-05-07T16:05:32-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 103, "id": 1461942, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Darkicon", "body": "Easy solo as a 352 MM hunter. Had to do it twice in a row technically thanks to my video card overheating and crashing at 50k HP left. Only used 60 FR.\n\nI just ran circles around her the entire time with Aspect of the Fox. Kept Serpent Sting at all times and kept above 90% with Chimera Shot. A couple times I accidentally walked too close to her tail and got knocked back. Killed her with 5 minutes left on the timer.\n\nI'm very much not used to circling bosses with Aspect of the Fox the entire time, so if I can solo her, any hunter can. You also don't need a beetle or turtle, she doesn't do nearly enough damage.", "date": "2011-07-05T23:28:25-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-05T23:30:56-05:00", 3, "Darkicon"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 104, "id": 1472597, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "355072", "body": "Soloed as ret paladin with 359 average ilvl. I had 3 minutes left in the berserk timer when she was down.\n\nI used Resistance Aura and Seal of Insight to get more survivability. Use 3 hp World of Glory as much as possible and Flash of Light once in a while, thanks to Seal of Insight you won't have so much problems with mana. Also use cooldowns when needed and Divine Protection/Holy Radiance when they are off cooldown. And try to heal alot when sacred shield procs and before Sapphiron freezes you in the air phase.\n\nSapphiron hits about 9k on plate (no shield) and about 10k with cleave.", "date": "2011-07-17T16:26:57-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-17T16:30:48-05:00", 1, "355072"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 105, "id": 1550980, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "534473", "body": "I don't know how long this bug has been in place, but for people with low self healing such as warriors, you can use the teleporter just as she moves for an air phase, bandage outside, then teleport back in just after the breath but just before she lands (use DBM timers). This has some strange effects on the fight:\r\n\r\n-Her health doesn't reset because she doesn't need a target in air phases (but it will if you are too slow getting back in after the breath)\r\n-She will ice block you inbetween the air phases and sit there trying to melee you (but getting loads of immune messages)\r\n-Provided you do not move out of the entrance area in her lair the blizzard will not despawn. If you move in, it will despawn anyway after you have been blocked for 15 seconds or so.\r\n\r\nOn the other hand it's probably not possible to beat the enrage using this method (unless that timer resets too).", "date": "2011-10-22T10:16:45-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 106, "id": 1574927, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheHeroOfTheDawn", "body": "Soloing this is... interesting.\r\nThe enrage is what's likely to kill you.\r\nIn order to beat it, you need to pull 4,648.333333333333 DPS on the boss-- for all 900 seconds of the fight.\r\n\r\nComplicating that are two things: \r\n1. The Air Phase-- every 45s, it knocks about 15s off of your 900- if you're a DK, make sure to get Diseases up for this if possible. With that in mind you only really have about ... 10 minutes of DPS time. (an approximation based on observation)... this alone raises the DPS requirement to about 6972 DPS (Assuming 0 DPS during Air Phase)\r\n2. The Curse-- Every 24s, it accounts for 15K of Healing on the boss.  Over the course of the fight, assuming zero resists, zero AMS and other negating mechanics, this will be cast-- based on math, a maximum of 37 times-- effectively increasing the boss's HP by ~555000.  With no fluxuations, you're looking at a DPS requirement of 7898 to beat the 'zerk timer-- so set your eyes on that number there. Beat that and you're golden.\r\n \r\nNote that the numbers don't account for random fluxuations nor does it account for the fact that Sapph doesn't cast the curse during Air Phase. \r\n\r\nOutside of that, I found that after two 'zerk wipes as a Blood DK, just freaking stand in the blizzard-- the damage done is very minimal, and it gives vengeance. Just know your self-heals and it's goooood.", "date": "2011-11-18T08:19:03-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 107, "id": 1603039, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ixianwarrior", "body": "Just soloed this guy as a Blood DK with full dps gear (e-ilvl 377), and still have over 9 minutes left on his enrage (pulled 12.3k dps).\r\n\r\nNone of his abilities present any threat, his life drain, melee, icebolt/frost tomb will not hurt you at all. The Blizzard he does does hurt a little (used a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=58143]Prismatic Elixir[/url]) but it won't bring you below 80% throughtough the encounter. The Frost tombs cannot be AMS'd / Every man for himself.\r\n\r\nHis life drain healed him for 150k hp, and he pulled an amazing 1400 dps on me, with Frost aura being 25% of all damage taken and Blizzard being 50%.\r\n\r\nWill also attempt the 25 man version, but it seems 14.5-15k dps is a minimum to beat him, and he has a little extra more self healing - definitely seems duoable but I'm unsure of any extra mechanics in such a group.", "date": "2011-12-28T07:35:08-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 108, "id": 1604735, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Scourgepretzels", "body": "Ok idk about you guys but i just killed her (2manned) with my 85 friend and we had'nt done the military and the construct quarters yet.did they change it so you can just skip straight to her or was it glitched or something?", "date": "2011-12-31T15:01:25-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, it has been nerfed - you may now engage Sapphiron immediately, without clearing any other wings. Please read the other comments on here.", "creationdate": "2012-07-09T16:50:32-05:00", "id": 555608, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1604735, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Alistair", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
